WEBVTT

00:00.162 --> 00:05.508
Well, we're going to be continuing this morning with our series on Long Journey Home.

00:06.029 --> 00:16.901
And if you haven't been with us for it up to this point, what we're looking at is the journey of the children of Israel from their time of slavery in Egypt on their way to their promised land.

00:17.361 --> 00:25.010
And in looking at that journey again, we've been looking for some of the connections it has between the Old Testament and the New Testament.

00:25.218 --> 00:28.722
and the connection that has to our own journey as followers of Jesus.

00:28.822 --> 00:29.964
What can we learn from that?

00:30.444 --> 00:32.947
And just looking at different incidents from that journey.

00:33.748 --> 00:37.112
Now, this last summer, we went through the minor prophets.

00:37.172 --> 00:38.414
Maybe remember that series.

00:38.834 --> 00:50.188
And I made the point then that the minor prophets are not minor because what they said wasn't important is just that they were very short books, as opposed to the longer prophets like Isaiah, Ezekiel, Jeremiah.

00:51.009 --> 00:54.994
One of the books that we looked at was authored by a man named

00:55.138 --> 00:55.859
Hosea.

00:56.860 --> 01:02.245
And this morning we're going to consider some of the life story of another Hosea.

01:03.226 --> 01:04.527
This guy is not a prophet.

01:05.388 --> 01:11.634
Rather, he was one of Moses's, maybe Moses's prime assistant.

01:12.514 --> 01:18.760
Now, if you're a Bible student, you may be thinking, I don't recall Moses having an assistant named Hosea.

01:18.780 --> 01:22.184
And that's only because you know him by his nickname.

01:22.944 --> 01:24.786
This comes from Numbers chapter 13.

01:25.538 --> 01:35.335
These were the names of the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land, and Moses called Hosea or Hosea, the son of none, Joshua.

01:36.477 --> 01:43.630
So who we know as Joshua, his original name was Hosea or Hosea.

01:44.472 --> 01:48.018
So how did Hosea get turned into

01:48.162 --> 01:49.023
Joshua.

01:49.143 --> 01:51.386
How did you get from one name to the other?

01:51.626 --> 01:54.309
And I'm going to give you a little Hebrew lesson this morning.

01:54.329 --> 01:55.791
We're going to take a look at two names.

01:56.291 --> 01:58.434
The first name being this name, Hosea.

01:58.794 --> 01:59.995
That's what it looks like in Hebrew.

02:00.476 --> 02:03.179
And the second one being the name Yahweh.

02:03.739 --> 02:05.281
And that's what that looks like in Hebrew.

02:05.521 --> 02:09.706
Now, Hosea means he delivers, okay?

02:10.167 --> 02:12.249
Or he saves.

02:12.269 --> 02:15.973
And that name Yahweh is the covenant name of God.

02:15.993 --> 02:16.754
It is the

02:16.866 --> 02:18.468
I am name.

02:18.488 --> 02:24.256
The name first appears when Moses encounters God at the burning bush.

02:24.276 --> 02:25.178
You recall that story?

02:25.198 --> 02:26.760
This comes from Exodus chapter three.

02:26.780 --> 02:35.532
Then Moses said to God, if I come to the people of Israel and say to them, the God of your fathers has sent me to you and they asked me, what is his name?

02:35.973 --> 02:37.054
What shall I say to them?

02:37.755 --> 02:40.439
God said to Moses, I am who I am.

02:40.499 --> 02:45.586
And he said, say this to the people of Israel, I am has sent me

02:45.666 --> 02:49.110
to you and that's where this name Yahweh comes from.

02:49.851 --> 02:56.418
It was a name that the Jews held in such reverence that when they were reading scriptures they would never speak the name aloud.

02:56.458 --> 03:01.804
And in place of that they would put in the word Adonai or Lord.

03:02.505 --> 03:05.228
And we still find a nod to this in our English Bibles.

03:05.288 --> 03:10.194
If you're in reading and you see the word Lord but it's in small caps

03:10.594 --> 03:11.555
That's what they've done.

03:11.595 --> 03:19.263
They've taken that word Yahweh, and they have substituted the word Lord, like the Jews are doing reading it.

03:19.663 --> 03:22.246
But they've let you know that by putting in small caps there.

03:22.346 --> 03:25.389
So we still kind of observe that custom.

03:26.670 --> 03:32.376
Now I want you to watch what happens when you take these two names and you start doing some merging.

03:33.177 --> 03:36.320
The first thing we're going to do is we're going to get rid of the vowel pointing.

03:36.340 --> 03:38.642
And I know you're worried about that, right?

03:39.010 --> 03:42.876
What the vowel pointing is in Hebrew, Hebrew originally didn't have any vowels in it.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.080
I mean, there were vowels, they just weren't written.

03:45.862 --> 03:47.825
And in fact, all the letters ran together.

03:47.845 --> 03:49.367
They didn't break between their words.

03:49.407 --> 03:51.150
You just have a stream of consonants.

03:51.912 --> 03:54.316
What you can understand, the problem is that it could make over time.

03:54.356 --> 03:56.019
As long as you know the context, you're fine.

03:56.559 --> 04:00.386
But if you forget the context, let's just take the letters BGN.

04:01.207 --> 04:02.129
What is BGN?

04:02.570 --> 04:03.651
Is that big one?

04:03.671 --> 04:05.234
Is that be gone?

04:05.314 --> 04:07.417
is that a lot of different ways you could read that.

04:07.457 --> 04:14.586
And so the scribes became concerned that future generations might forget what the right vowels were to put the right letters.

04:14.786 --> 04:23.698
Because they didn't want to add anything to God's word, they decided that they would create a vowel system that went above and below the consonants.

04:24.339 --> 04:33.010
So when you read Hebrew, you read from right to left, and you read top to bottom, and those little dots and dashes, those are the vowels.

04:33.314 --> 04:37.439
So for our purposes, we're just gonna get rid of those, okay?

04:37.459 --> 04:45.069
Now, all of Jose's birth name, we find it in his new name, Joshua.

04:46.130 --> 04:53.560
But then also, the covenant name of God, Yahweh, the first part of that gets merged in as well.

04:54.561 --> 05:01.650
And what you end up with is a name that means Yahweh delivers, or Joshua.

05:02.882 --> 05:10.513
Do you recall what the angel told Mary, actually what he told Joseph about the baby that Mary was going to have?

05:10.974 --> 05:12.536
This comes from Matthew chapter one.

05:12.596 --> 05:22.151
Says, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream saying, Joseph, son of David, do not fear to take Mary as your wife for that which is conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.

05:22.691 --> 05:32.466
She will bear a son and you shall call his name Jesus, which is Yaisu, which is the same in Greek as Joshua.

05:32.802 --> 05:38.311
You'll call his name Jesus or Joshua, for he will save his people from their sin.

05:38.351 --> 05:39.573
You see, there's the meaning again.

05:40.294 --> 05:44.180
You're gonna give him this name and the name means God saves.

05:45.623 --> 05:52.473
Now to me, the fact that Moses upgraded Joshua's name in that way, tells me right away that he saw something special about this young man.

05:53.235 --> 05:56.780
There was something that distinguished Joshua in the eyes of Moses.

05:57.482 --> 06:00.306
So what do we know about Joshua?

06:00.418 --> 06:11.514
The giving of his upgraded name isn't explained until we get to the account of the spies being sent into the Promised Land, but the fact was Joshua had been distinguishing himself long before that ever happened.

06:12.455 --> 06:22.309
The first mention of Joshua is in the book of Exodus when he was tasked by Moses with assembling the militia to go and fight against the marauding Amalekites.

06:22.449 --> 06:24.292
We looked at that a few weeks ago if you recall.

06:25.694 --> 06:28.498
But in Numbers 11, 28, we find this little phrase.

06:29.666 --> 06:34.313
Joshua, the son of none, the assistant of Moses from his youth.

06:35.414 --> 06:46.090
So from the time Joshua was a young man, Moses had seen something in him that said, this is a guy that I want to be working with me, closely with me, my protege, if you will.

06:47.292 --> 06:52.420
Now, this, of course, occurred a number of years after Israel had completed their conquest of the Promised Land.

06:52.520 --> 06:59.570
Oh, this is, so the question is, how old was Joshua when he started serving as Moses' assistant?

07:00.770 --> 07:04.957
We don't get a lot of clues as to Joshua's age except this one.

07:05.578 --> 07:10.185
After these things, Joshua, the son of none, the servant of the Lord, died being 110 years old.

07:10.566 --> 07:14.812
That's the only definite marker we get as to how old Joshua was at some point.

07:14.892 --> 07:19.660
And this, of course, comes a number of years after Israel has come into the Promised Land.

07:20.722 --> 07:28.434
Another marker people sometimes point to is the age of Caleb at the time he was sent on his spying mission into the Promised Land.

07:28.866 --> 07:29.867
This is what Caleb said.

07:30.047 --> 07:35.954
Caleb says, I was 40 years old when Moses, the servant of the Lord, sent me from Kedish Barnia to spy out the land.

07:36.654 --> 07:49.929
And since Joshua and Caleb appear side by side as the two faithful spies who alone were permitted to enter the promised land, a lot of folks conclude that, well, Joshua must have been about the same age as Caleb.

07:50.469 --> 07:51.891
That's just an assumption.

07:51.911 --> 07:54.834
There's nothing in the text that says that.

07:54.946 --> 08:06.798
If so, that would mean that Joshua had started assisting Moses sometime in his mid to late thirties, if you do the math, which doesn't really sound like what you would describe as a youth.

08:07.839 --> 08:12.103
I ran across an article by a Jewish rabbi, and he proposes another age.

08:12.323 --> 08:17.629
And if he's right, it helps to answer a kind of puzzling passage that you run into.

08:17.669 --> 08:22.113
And I understand this is a complete Bible nerd detour we're going on here, all right?

08:22.153 --> 08:23.154
But just bear with me.

08:23.842 --> 08:29.149
This guy's name is Alejo Schatz and he gets his clues from this passage in Numbers 14.

08:29.850 --> 08:34.717
And this is where God declares his judgment on the unbelieving generation.

08:35.598 --> 08:39.323
Now we looked at this story last week and we talked about what happened at Kedish Barnia, right?

08:39.343 --> 08:40.504
They get to Kedish Barnia.

08:40.865 --> 08:42.427
They decided to spend the spies in.

08:42.487 --> 08:47.254
Eight of the spies come back saying, he has the beautiful lamb, but there's not a chance that we can take it.

08:47.294 --> 08:49.577
They've got these fortified skyscrapers.

08:49.597 --> 08:50.698
There's giants in the land.

08:51.319 --> 08:53.522
Two of the spies, Joshua and Caleb say,

08:53.890 --> 08:55.732
We can do this because God is with us.

08:56.152 --> 09:00.557
And you're calling us at that point that God sends Israel in that 40-year detour.

09:00.577 --> 09:06.063
He says, none of this generation is going to enter the land only your children are going to get to go.

09:06.103 --> 09:10.247
The only exceptions, of course, being Caleb and Joshua.

09:10.547 --> 09:14.651
And then you get these two passages and see if you can spot what seems odd.

09:14.992 --> 09:18.095
These are both in the same chapter within just a few verses of each other.

09:19.656 --> 09:21.138
This from Numbers 14.

09:22.146 --> 09:39.931
None of the men who've seen my glory and my signs that I did in Egypt and the wilderness and yet have put me to the test these ten times and have not obeyed my voice shall see the land that I swore to give to their fathers and none of those who despise me'll sure see it but my servant Caleb because he has a different spirit.

09:40.812 --> 09:43.335
Okay, now you jump down just a few verses and you find this.

09:44.657 --> 09:48.242
All your number listed in the census from 20 years old and upward

09:48.450 --> 10:00.468
who have grumbled against me, not one, shall come into the land where I swore that I would make you dwell, except Caleb, the son of Jefana, and Joshua, the son of none.

10:01.690 --> 10:03.433
Do you see the little weirdness there?

10:03.473 --> 10:07.779
In verse 24, the only person mentioned is Caleb.

10:08.360 --> 10:11.926
And then in verse 30, it says Caleb and Joshua.

10:12.607 --> 10:13.488
So what happened?

10:13.508 --> 10:17.554
Did Moses just forget the first time to include Joshua?

10:17.794 --> 10:19.837
Here's what this rabbi proposes.

10:19.937 --> 10:21.138
I think it makes a lot of sense.

10:22.120 --> 10:23.421
He points to this first passage.

10:24.002 --> 10:30.050
And what it says is, none of the men who have seen my glory and my signs that I did in Egypt.

10:31.051 --> 10:41.125
And then in the second one, he talks about all your number listed in the census from 20 years old and upward, not one of them shall come into the land.

10:42.246 --> 10:45.170
Okay, so when was the census taken?

10:45.698 --> 10:48.461
We find this in Numbers 1, verses 1 through 3.

10:48.501 --> 10:51.464
The Lord tells Moses to take a census.

10:51.764 --> 10:57.230
And the cutoff point for separating the men from the boys is 20 years old and upward.

10:57.250 --> 11:00.694
If you're under 20, you didn't get counted in the census.

11:00.714 --> 11:02.756
If you're above 20, then you get counted.

11:03.937 --> 11:08.041
And what this rabbi suggests is that Caleb was older than Joshua.

11:08.862 --> 11:12.466
That Caleb was above the age of 20, while the people were still in Egypt.

11:12.706 --> 11:13.647
So he was a man.

11:13.847 --> 11:20.153
The Lord said, none of the men who were in Egypt who saw my miracles and yet still have doubted me, none of those men are going to enter.

11:21.274 --> 11:28.602
But then when the census is taken, two years after leaving Egypt, he proposes that Joshua had turned 20.

11:29.502 --> 11:35.208
And so the Lord says, none of those in the census will enter except Joshua and Caleb.

11:35.228 --> 11:39.172
You see that group would include Joshua, the first group would not.

11:40.393 --> 11:41.234
If that is right,

11:41.570 --> 11:43.673
because I know you're dying to find out, Tim, what is your point?

11:44.273 --> 11:56.729
If that is true, what it tells us is that Joshua probably started serving Moses when he was about 19 years old, which would fit this description of him serving Moses from the time he was a youth.

11:57.430 --> 12:02.977
He was a young man who early in life was chosen by Moses to be an assistant.

12:04.739 --> 12:10.546
I think there's something worth thinking about in light of Joshua's young age, because what we see is

12:11.106 --> 12:18.955
A man who from an early age was available and engaged and willing for God to use him.

12:20.116 --> 12:21.657
He made himself available to Moses.

12:22.699 --> 12:26.563
When Moses needed someone to lead the charge, Joshua was there.

12:26.603 --> 12:29.326
Sarah mentioned this too.

12:29.386 --> 12:33.771
We find Joshua accompanying Moses in some very holy moments.

12:34.532 --> 12:38.776
This from Exodus 24, the Lord said to Moses, come up to me on the mountain and wait there.

12:38.796 --> 12:40.498
This is being called with Mount Sinai.

12:40.834 --> 12:45.041
that I may give you the tablets of stone with the law and the commandments, which I've written for their instruction.

12:45.081 --> 12:48.747
So Moses rose with his assistant Joshua.

12:49.869 --> 12:51.892
Joshua gets to go up with Moses.

12:53.014 --> 12:59.284
Or this, the thing that Sarah referred to, Moses used to take the tin and pitch it outside the camp, far from the camp.

12:59.765 --> 13:00.927
He called it the tin of meeting.

13:01.468 --> 13:05.234
Everyone who saw the Lord would go out to the tin of meeting, which was outside the camp.

13:05.954 --> 13:10.939
When Moses entered the tent, the pillar of cloud would descend and stand at the entrance, and the Lord would speak with Moses.

13:11.419 --> 13:15.904
Thus the Lord used to speak to Moses face to face as a man speaks to his friend.

13:16.885 --> 13:25.833
When Moses turned again into the camp, his assistant Joshua, the son of none, a young man would not depart from the tent.

13:28.075 --> 13:34.802
The picture begins to form for you is that there is this young person who seriously cares about the things of God

13:35.042 --> 13:35.923
and the people of God.

13:37.205 --> 13:46.900
When the time comes, 40 years later, that God tells Moses to appoint Joshua as his successor, Joshua's fitness for service does not arise out of a vacuum.

13:48.402 --> 13:55.973
I don't know if Josh had any sense of what his future role might be, but the fact was he had been preparing himself for a long time.

13:58.698 --> 14:04.306
Thinking about the New Testament, I have no doubt that the Apostle Paul would have applauded

14:04.482 --> 14:09.350
a young Joshua, just like he encouraged his young protege, Timothy.

14:10.551 --> 14:11.974
Paul said these words to Timothy.

14:11.994 --> 14:14.057
He said, let no one despise you for your youth.

14:14.978 --> 14:22.931
But set the believers an example in speech, in conduct, in love, in faith, in purity.

14:24.573 --> 14:30.022
Paul in that same letter suggests something that an up-and-coming leader, like Timothy, might aspire to.

14:30.042 --> 14:32.786
He says, the saying is trustworthy.

14:33.282 --> 14:40.814
If anyone aspires to the office of overseer, he desires a noble task.

14:40.834 --> 14:41.395
Ambition.

14:42.958 --> 14:44.120
The drive to succeed.

14:45.903 --> 14:48.788
Is it a healthy thing for a Christian?

14:48.808 --> 14:52.093
Is it a healthy thing in the church to be ambitious?

14:53.776 --> 14:55.519
Our world is full of ambitious people.

14:56.600 --> 14:59.986
I've known students who from the time they were in junior high,

15:00.546 --> 15:05.394
Sometimes even younger had set their sights on attending an elite military academy.

15:05.434 --> 15:08.859
Maybe they wanted to go to Annapolis or West Point or the Air Force Academy.

15:08.939 --> 15:16.351
And everything they did was geared toward getting that appointment, to get into that academy.

15:17.132 --> 15:18.134
That was their ambition.

15:18.194 --> 15:22.721
And of course, getting that academy was just a stepping stone to a higher goal.

15:23.803 --> 15:25.746
They aspired to become an officer.

15:25.786 --> 15:28.370
And in attaining that dream,

15:28.450 --> 15:40.045
They started to aggressively shape their resume to get higher ranks, seek out the right postings, get the right credentials, earn the ribbons that will hopefully propel them to a higher rank.

15:41.046 --> 15:54.002
Maybe they dream one day of being a general or an admiral themselves, or maybe they're looking beyond their military career, and they think about the doors that could open for them in politics or in industry if they have enough accomplishments behind them.

15:55.970 --> 16:01.077
or maybe it's a bright young computer programmer trying to climb the ranks of Silicon Valley.

16:02.058 --> 16:13.534
Bouncing from one venture capital startup to the next, trying to ricochet their way to the top of the corporate ladder, putting in those 80 to 100 hour weeks to keep themselves in the cutting edge of technology.

16:14.856 --> 16:18.962
Because if you get there, if you prove yourself, the rewards can be immense.

16:19.522 --> 16:29.155
Maybe you saw a few weeks ago, Mark Zuckerberg just signed a 24-year-old AI researcher to a four-year, $250 million contract.

16:30.337 --> 16:31.298
Not bad for being 24.

16:34.262 --> 16:35.284
But of course, you know how it goes.

16:36.726 --> 16:45.778
The tales are legion of ambitious people who have shipwrecked lives, casualties of their ambitions run amok.

16:46.754 --> 17:00.713
marriages that get ruined, children who are estranged, feel abandoned, colleagues who get alienated in a dog eat dog race for the top, personal lives demonstrated mentally, physically, spiritually.

17:00.753 --> 17:13.650
And you understand why Jesus said, what does a prophet, a man or a woman, to gain the whole world, to achieve all of your ambitions and yet lose your own soul?

17:16.194 --> 17:19.298
So it's no wonder that ambition is often viewed with skepticism.

17:20.739 --> 17:26.306
The fear that we become somehow a modern day version of the mythical Icarus.

17:26.326 --> 17:26.986
Remember Icarus?

17:27.026 --> 17:39.641
He was the guy who built himself some wings out of feathers and wax and was so ecstatic over his ability to fly that he flew higher and higher until he flew too close to the sun, melted his wings and fell to his death.

17:42.844 --> 17:44.306
But not all ambition is bad.

17:45.698 --> 17:51.244
Motivation is a powerful tool for good when it's focused on the right goal and when it's kept within the right bounds.

17:52.245 --> 17:58.513
And Paul here recommends a specific kind of ambition, an ambition to become a leader among God's people.

18:00.815 --> 18:09.725
Of course, I think we've all seen the damage that's been brought by some Christian leaders who've been motivated by misplaced ambition.

18:11.187 --> 18:13.970
Because you can have lots of misplaced ambition within the church.

18:15.426 --> 18:20.995
leaders who pursue a set of criteria that in the world's eyes signify a great leader.

18:22.538 --> 18:41.490
Big attendance at your church services, big budgets, big building programs, best selling books, speaking tours, TV, radio, social media, influence, all those markers, all those metrics that we can look at and say, now there is a leader of great significance.

18:43.298 --> 18:50.066
And I'd say that none of those things in themselves are bad, except when they become the goal of our ambitions.

18:51.348 --> 18:59.939
When externals become more important than internals, people who end up using the church to fuel their egos and enrich their bank accounts.

19:01.581 --> 19:07.488
See, Paul didn't see anything wrong with a young person being ambitious for leadership, but only if that ambition had the right goals.

19:08.750 --> 19:12.114
And in suggesting it's a good thing to desire leadership in the church,

19:12.386 --> 19:15.090
Paul immediately then lists his metrics for greatness.

19:16.111 --> 19:22.940
And none of them have anything to do with congregation size or books written or funds raised.

19:23.982 --> 19:30.610
Rather, what he lists are metrics of character, a focus on who we're becoming on the inside.

19:32.373 --> 19:36.659
He lists 14 essential godly traits of a godly leader.

19:38.201 --> 19:42.226
The traits, and you can read them, read his letter to Timothy, but they include

19:42.402 --> 19:56.978
demonstrated integrity, faithfulness, self-control, a generous, gentle, hospitable spirit, a growing knowledge of God's Word that would allow them to teach others.

19:57.078 --> 20:11.634
And from all the clues that we can pick up about Joshua, I think we see a young man living generations before Paul's protege, Timothy, who was aspiring to develop and was demonstrating those kinds of traits.

20:12.354 --> 20:16.678
He was a man of growing character because he had a great love for God.

20:19.181 --> 20:22.865
So I guess I put a challenge out to any of you who are south of middle age.

20:24.166 --> 20:31.093
The challenge would be that you consider what it means to prepare yourself to serve and to lead.

20:33.175 --> 20:40.402
Recent statistics say that the church in America is facing a leadership crisis because there aren't enough young pastors to meet the need.

20:41.666 --> 20:44.571
But of course, pastors are just one level of leadership within the church.

20:45.352 --> 20:49.398
For the body of Christ of function, there are leaders needed in all kinds of other areas.

20:50.279 --> 21:00.936
It might be serving as a lay leader, a deacon on a ministry team, teaching a Sunday school class, being a counselor at a youth camp, leading in worship, leading in a home Bible study, serving as a church elder.

21:03.840 --> 21:04.882
I would say to all of us,

21:05.666 --> 21:10.512
not only to the young, to aspire to something to benefit the body of Christ.

21:10.532 --> 21:19.102
And in doing that, aspire not to achieve greatness, but aspire to become the kind of person that God can use as a great leader.

21:20.344 --> 21:23.828
I'd also say that those are the kind of spiritual leaders that we should follow.

21:25.130 --> 21:30.637
It's really easy to get our attention turned to just big names and popular people.

21:31.818 --> 21:35.122
And there's nothing wrong with someone being popular.

21:36.546 --> 21:38.909
But we should always be looking to say, what is the character?

21:38.969 --> 21:41.112
Who are the leaders that I'm following?

21:41.373 --> 21:44.998
Are they men and women of true godly character?

21:45.058 --> 21:47.942
What difference does that make?

21:48.923 --> 21:50.826
Well, we find this from the end of Joshua's life.

21:51.347 --> 21:55.532
Joshua, the son of none, the servant of the Lord, died being 110 years old.

21:56.474 --> 22:00.219
And Israel served the Lord all the days of Joshua.

22:01.921 --> 22:03.043
You see, the impact of his life.

22:04.264 --> 22:05.426
He was a man, a character.

22:06.210 --> 22:15.245
who led well, led with character, and the impact it had on the generation that he led, was it helped them to follow God well also.

22:18.550 --> 22:28.326
As I was studying on the life of Joshua, I ran into an episode that quite honestly, I had almost forgotten about it, and it just kind of jumped out at me, and I wanna take us there.

22:28.366 --> 22:33.234
This happens many years later, Moses has died,

22:33.346 --> 22:36.389
Joshua has assumed his role as leader of the nation.

22:37.230 --> 22:43.898
The nation has just crossed over the boundary into the Promised Land, and they've celebrated their first Passover in the Land.

22:45.039 --> 22:49.444
And now they're on the cusp of their first great battle of conquest.

22:49.564 --> 22:53.589
They are about to go up against the walled city of Jericho.

22:54.790 --> 22:55.932
And suddenly this happens.

22:56.152 --> 22:57.954
It comes from Joshua chapter five.

22:59.776 --> 23:01.618
When Joshua was by Jericho,

23:02.434 --> 23:09.764
He lifted up his eyes and looked and behold, a man was standing before him with his drawn sword in his hand.

23:11.547 --> 23:16.874
And Joshua went to him and said to him, are you for us or for our adversaries?

23:18.677 --> 23:20.539
And he said, no.

23:21.881 --> 23:24.425
But I am the commander of the army of the Lord.

23:25.546 --> 23:27.089
Now I have come.

23:28.771 --> 23:30.994
And Joshua fell on his face to the earth

23:31.426 --> 23:36.073
and worshiped and said to him, what does my Lord say to his servant?

23:37.796 --> 23:46.168
And the commander of the Lord's army said to Joshua, take off your sandals from your feet for the place where you are standing is holy.

23:47.210 --> 23:48.291
And Joshua did so.

23:51.136 --> 23:51.957
So who was that?

23:51.997 --> 23:55.442
This mysterious figure suddenly shows up.

23:55.810 --> 23:59.395
and identifies himself as the commander of the Lord's army.

23:59.435 --> 24:13.296
And there's something about this man's presence that is deeply unsettling to Joshua because his immediate impulse when this mysterious commander identifies himself is to fall flat on his face in worship.

24:14.739 --> 24:17.222
And one thought might be, well, it was an angel.

24:17.783 --> 24:24.914
Maybe it was an angel that appeared to Joshua, but know what happened or rather what didn't happen when Joshua prostrated himself.

24:25.762 --> 24:30.407
Joshua falls on his face and the commander does not tell him to get up again.

24:31.669 --> 24:32.410
He leaves him there.

24:33.851 --> 24:39.178
Now consider that compared to a similar story we have all the way up in the book of Revelation.

24:40.779 --> 24:49.229
John is confronted here by a powerful angel and John says, I fell down to worship at the feet of the angel, but he said to me, you must not do that.

24:50.170 --> 24:53.394
I'm a fellow servant with you, worship God.

24:54.722 --> 24:58.847
So a person falls down to worship in front of an angel and the angel says, don't do that.

24:59.908 --> 25:04.634
Joshua falls down in front of the command of the Lord's army and the commander just leaves in there.

25:06.577 --> 25:12.985
And then there's this whole thing about taking off your sandals because where your standing is holy ground.

25:14.086 --> 25:17.190
Remember any place else that that kind of language has been used?

25:19.293 --> 25:19.873
Burning Bush.

25:20.694 --> 25:23.698
Moses encounters this manifestation of God's presence.

25:24.322 --> 25:26.245
And the Lord says to him, take off your shoes.

25:26.766 --> 25:29.009
Take off your sandals, you're standing on holy ground.

25:30.351 --> 25:37.782
In other words, this mysterious commander seems to be saying, if you're in my presence, you're in the presence of the Lord.

25:39.404 --> 25:42.188
I think this is what theologians call a Christophany.

25:42.929 --> 25:46.695
Fancy word, it just means an Old Testament appearance of Jesus.

25:47.616 --> 25:51.762
We have a few instances where a mysterious figure like that appears in the Old Testament.

25:52.130 --> 25:55.154
in ways that seem uniquely fitted to Jesus.

25:56.296 --> 26:01.864
When it comes to being the commander of the Lord's army, that is certainly description that fits Jesus uniquely.

26:02.145 --> 26:03.246
Again, this revelation.

26:04.428 --> 26:07.633
Then I saw heaven open and behold a white horse.

26:07.653 --> 26:12.740
The one sitting on it is called faithful and true, and in righteousness he judges and makes war.

26:13.782 --> 26:19.410
The armies of heaven, arrayed in fine linen, white and pure, were following him on white horses.

26:20.130 --> 26:27.378
On his robe and on his thigh, he has a name written, King of Kings and Lord of Lords.

26:30.041 --> 26:31.022
I think Jesus showed up.

26:32.823 --> 26:36.567
Joshua was about to enter into a time of intense conflict.

26:37.989 --> 26:39.190
There were battles to be fought.

26:40.892 --> 26:46.578
The thing that gave him courage was the divine promise that God was with him.

26:47.490 --> 26:55.500
Remember when Joshua first assumed his role of leadership, one of the things that the Lord's system repeatedly is, do not be afraid.

26:56.622 --> 26:59.105
Take courage, I am with you.

27:01.748 --> 27:15.826
Which means me wonder why when that is what has given Joshua the courage, the courage to be the one spy who brought back a faithful word, the courage to step into the big shoes that Moses had left, the courage to cross that Jordan, why is it

27:15.906 --> 27:23.936
that right at this point, when Joshua needs all the assurance he can get, would the command of the Lord's army show up with a message like this?

27:25.358 --> 27:27.300
Joshua says, whose side are you on?

27:28.462 --> 27:31.846
Wouldn't you expect the Lord to say, Joshua, don't worry buddy, I'm on your side 100%.

27:31.946 --> 27:39.095
Instead, the commander says, I'm not on your side.

27:41.538 --> 27:44.562
I can only assume God wanted to make it clear that his support

27:44.930 --> 27:52.119
and his blessing were only with Joshua as long as Joshua was aligned with the agenda and the priorities of the Lord.

27:53.601 --> 27:58.827
Joshua couldn't assume God's help just by virtue of him being the leader of Israel.

28:00.849 --> 28:07.277
You only have to look at the later history of Israel long after Joshua's time to see what happens when people get this wrong.

28:08.038 --> 28:10.161
Again, we looked at the minor prophets this summer.

28:10.201 --> 28:14.386
Let me take you to just one thing out of the book of Micah, this from Micah chapter three,

28:15.810 --> 28:17.592
Listen to me, you leaders of Israel.

28:18.574 --> 28:21.738
You hate justice and you twist all that is right.

28:22.859 --> 28:26.564
And yet, all of you claim to depend on the Lord.

28:27.885 --> 28:31.951
No harm can come to us, you say, for the Lord is here among us.

28:32.792 --> 28:34.334
Hear what they're saying, God is on our side.

28:35.715 --> 28:39.981
Because of you, Jerusalem will be reduced to ruins.

28:41.342 --> 28:44.146
The Lord says to their leaders, you got this a little mixed up.

28:44.994 --> 28:48.880
You think that somehow the default position is that I will always take your side.

28:50.022 --> 28:53.667
But the problem is, you're not doing things my way.

28:55.791 --> 28:58.936
See, God was with Joshua as long as he was fighting God's way.

28:58.976 --> 29:02.682
The question is never is God on our side.

29:03.823 --> 29:06.387
The question is always, are we on his?

29:08.450 --> 29:13.298
And the sobering message to Joshua was that the commander of the Lord's army

29:14.114 --> 29:15.796
was not under Joshua's command.

29:17.919 --> 29:26.351
I've been saying all along in this series, there are a lot of parallels between Israel's physical during the wilderness and our spiritual journey as followers of Jesus.

29:27.973 --> 29:31.137
And like Israel, we too face conflict and foes.

29:31.217 --> 29:35.784
It's not hard to make those connections, but they are different foes.

29:37.205 --> 29:39.429
Israel was facing physical foes.

29:40.951 --> 29:43.474
Our foes are not the same, which means our fight

29:43.842 --> 29:45.925
has to be on completely different terms.

29:47.067 --> 29:49.530
You know the passage well comes out of Ephesians chapter six.

29:49.631 --> 29:59.105
We're not fighting against flesh and blood enemies, but against evil rulers and authorities of the unseen world, against mighty powers in this dark world and against evil spirits in the heavenly places.

30:00.988 --> 30:02.770
Our our battle is a spiritual battle.

30:04.513 --> 30:07.637
Jesus made the same distinction when he appeared before Pilate.

30:08.298 --> 30:13.426
Remember he's there before Pilate and Pilate's headquarters and Pilate says to him, are you the king of the Jews?

30:14.338 --> 30:17.784
Jesus answered, my kingdom is not of this world.

30:18.665 --> 30:28.020
If my kingdom were of this world, my servants would have been fighting that I might not be delivered over to the Jews, but my kingdom is not from this world.

30:29.402 --> 30:33.228
There is a fight to be had, Pilate, but it's not the fight you think it is.

30:34.350 --> 30:41.682
I am a king, but not the way you think about kings, not the way that you think about the political world.

30:44.002 --> 30:46.524
I sent out a survey a few weeks ago.

30:46.544 --> 30:47.645
A lot of you responded to that.

30:47.705 --> 30:48.446
Thank you very much.

30:48.666 --> 30:50.348
If you've been meaning to get around to it, it's too late.

30:52.870 --> 30:56.374
But I was asking you, what are things you would like to hear me teach on?

30:56.434 --> 30:57.354
What would you like me to address?

30:57.455 --> 30:58.536
And it was interesting.

30:58.556 --> 31:01.779
There was a lot of folks who came back and said, man, I wish you would talk about politics.

31:02.860 --> 31:04.741
And I can't think of a topic I like to talk about less.

31:07.944 --> 31:13.970
But I think we all know that these are very contentious times in our country when it comes to the world of politics.

31:15.138 --> 31:20.846
And specifically within the Christian world, there's this thing called Christian nationalism.

31:21.487 --> 31:35.547
Now people debate exactly what that term even means, but at its core I think what you find is this mixing of a robust nationalized America first allegiance combined with a loudly professed allegiance to Christ.

31:37.009 --> 31:40.914
And then you add to that a deep allegiance to partisan politics

31:41.378 --> 31:45.983
And you end up with something that I think both distorts the gospel to the world around us.

31:47.004 --> 31:50.708
And so often leads to some deep divisions and bitterness within the church.

31:51.989 --> 31:54.853
Friendships get ruined, families get divided.

31:57.015 --> 31:58.336
I've known churches that split.

31:59.698 --> 31:59.978
Why?

32:01.760 --> 32:07.346
Because I think a lot of us have bought into a mindset at times that says those who oppose us

32:08.578 --> 32:11.703
have to be vilified and heated and crushed.

32:12.744 --> 32:13.746
Because that's how you fight.

32:15.508 --> 32:16.650
It's all for good cause.

32:17.652 --> 32:19.795
It's all because we're hoping for a righteous end.

32:19.835 --> 32:26.044
And in a righteous end, maybe it justifies a few short-term unrighteous strategies.

32:28.147 --> 32:32.754
And all of it is rooted in a conviction that God is on our side.

32:34.466 --> 32:42.418
I came across a concept recently called motive attribution asymmetry, which a lot of big words, but it's pretty simple idea.

32:43.720 --> 32:50.830
It's when the hostility between people erupts, and both sides believe that they're being driven by love and their opponents by hate.

32:51.812 --> 32:52.773
You've probably seen that.

32:53.574 --> 32:56.098
Both sides suspect the worst of the other.

32:57.500 --> 33:01.446
And of course, if those I disagree with are hateful, well, that makes me angry.

33:02.408 --> 33:04.050
That makes me want to hate them back.

33:05.890 --> 33:16.626
Columnist Arthur Brooks and a recent op-ed suggested that when anger is combined with another very natural emotion discussed, that we end up with contempt.

33:17.487 --> 33:22.975
At a making this point, he recounts a conversation he once had with John Gottman, maybe no Gottman of the Gottman Institute.

33:23.035 --> 33:28.343
It's a famous counseling center dedicated to helping marriages.

33:28.423 --> 33:31.027
They have helped thousands of couples who have been facing divorce.

33:31.788 --> 33:33.010
And Gottman told him,

33:33.634 --> 33:40.666
He said he could usually tell within 15 minutes with 94% accuracy if a couple is going to make it.

33:41.848 --> 33:50.882
He said the key was when they discussed conflict, does either of them roll their eyes or otherwise display contempt for their partner?

33:52.285 --> 34:00.338
So if I see that one of them has contempt for their partner, the chance for that marriage to survive is pretty remote.

34:02.498 --> 34:05.281
I would say that certainly applies in the world of politics as well.

34:06.222 --> 34:14.693
When we view whole segments of our fellow citizens with contempt, it's very hard to find peace.

34:14.733 --> 34:16.795
It's very hard to share the gospel.

34:19.518 --> 34:25.906
As I talk with other pastors, this festering issue of political contempt within congregations comes up regularly.

34:27.458 --> 34:29.281
I'll give you one little example.

34:29.421 --> 34:35.811
I got an email a couple weeks ago from someone who is not a part of DCC, but they are highly active in these things.

34:36.492 --> 34:44.284
And he wanted me to know about an upcoming event on a current social hot-button issue, an issue which, by the way, he and I would agree on.

34:44.725 --> 34:45.947
So we want to talk about sides.

34:46.047 --> 34:47.309
I would be on his side.

34:48.450 --> 34:52.256
What was intriguing was the way he invited me to attend.

34:53.598 --> 34:55.922
This is the sum total of the messages I received.

34:57.282 --> 35:00.426
Do you care or are you a fraud?

35:02.469 --> 35:04.211
That was a compelling invitation right there.

35:06.814 --> 35:07.755
You can hear what he's saying.

35:08.877 --> 35:12.702
What he's saying is, come on, Tim, whose side are you on?

35:13.663 --> 35:14.885
There's no room for discussion.

35:15.866 --> 35:17.248
It's my way or the highway.

35:17.288 --> 35:18.409
It's us or them.

35:18.449 --> 35:25.298
It's the problem of political partisanship becoming equated with godliness.

35:25.922 --> 35:34.835
Back in 2018, the late Timothy Keller wrote an editorial in The New York Times titled, How Do Christians Fit Into the Two-Party System?

35:35.837 --> 35:36.338
They don't.

35:37.079 --> 35:38.721
Let me read you just one piece out of that.

35:40.825 --> 35:51.921
Another reason Christians these days cannot allow the church to be fully identified with any particular party is the problem of what British ethicist James Munford calls, package deal ethics.

35:52.803 --> 35:55.026
Increasingly, political parties insist

35:55.266 --> 36:00.654
that you cannot work on one issue with them if you don't embrace all of their approved positions.

36:03.338 --> 36:18.160
Over the past few years, I have had multiple people tell me that they have considered not coming to church because they're not comfortable being with people they realize may support one political position or another.

36:19.662 --> 36:22.226
And those comments have come from across the political spectrum.

36:22.562 --> 36:25.265
It's not just one side of those issues.

36:28.428 --> 36:36.557
Worse, even as I say that, there may be some of you, I hope few of you, but there may be some of you are thinking, well that's fine if they don't come.

36:37.758 --> 36:39.620
If they don't agree with me, they should stay home.

36:42.103 --> 36:45.507
And if that's anywhere in your heart, I would simply have to ask whose army you are in.

36:46.648 --> 36:47.569
Who is your commander?

36:49.051 --> 36:52.114
Do you realize when Jesus chose his 12 closest disciples

36:52.674 --> 37:03.809
after a full night of prayer that he included among them a zealot and a tax collector, you could not get farther apart on the political spectrum than a zealot and a tax collector.

37:03.849 --> 37:10.318
The zealots who wanted to violently overthrow the Romans and the tax collectors who made their living by collecting Rome's taxes.

37:12.241 --> 37:15.926
Jesus called them to something beyond those politics.

37:17.107 --> 37:19.090
He called them to follow him.

37:19.970 --> 37:24.656
And it turned out that following him put all of them at odds with their preferred political factions.

37:25.477 --> 37:34.047
Both the anti-government zealots and the pro-government tax collectors found themselves out of step with their people because they were in step with Jesus.

37:38.152 --> 37:42.077
I'll give you just one more illustration of how this kind of affects me sometimes.

37:43.619 --> 37:46.322
This summer we were doing that series on the minor prophets.

37:47.266 --> 37:57.101
And one of the things that came up over and over in the minor prophets are the ways that the rich and powerful were oppressing and abusing the poor and the weak.

37:57.121 --> 38:03.070
And the command of the Lord that I encountered over and over again was to do justice.

38:04.072 --> 38:06.756
We saw that in the past, we read earlier from Micah, right?

38:06.816 --> 38:16.210
Do you realize how often I wrestled over how best to discuss that concept?

38:16.802 --> 38:17.463
of justice.

38:19.066 --> 38:19.346
Why?

38:20.468 --> 38:33.809
Because I knew that preaching about social justice was apt to trigger some people to conclude, well, Tim must be woke, which would either make them super happy or super mad.

38:35.511 --> 38:42.482
Not because that conclusion was fueled by an allegiance to Jesus as much as it was trying to figure out if

38:42.562 --> 38:47.409
By using that word, I'm either affirming or repudiating their political agenda.

38:48.811 --> 38:57.985
Just by using the word justice, say, by the way, completely biblical word, some start asking internally, well, whose side is he on?

39:01.791 --> 39:09.202
My intent is never to push, either a woke or a mega-informed agenda.

39:10.690 --> 39:15.038
because I believe that both march lock step into some serious errors.

39:16.761 --> 39:23.634
My heart's desire is not to be on the left side or the right side, but by God's grace to be on His side.

39:25.578 --> 39:26.279
And please hear me.

39:27.161 --> 39:29.606
I don't say that with any sense of superiority.

39:30.768 --> 39:34.034
I am, as though I'm above all of that, because I am not.

39:34.402 --> 39:41.029
You get me fired up on the right topic and I am just as apt as the next guy to confidently say way more than I actually know.

39:46.194 --> 39:48.336
Jesus has had me on a journey these past few years.

39:50.478 --> 39:53.141
Here's what began to catch my attention in me.

39:54.963 --> 40:02.450
I began to detect this subtle tendency in my heart to defend, excuse, minimize,

40:02.530 --> 40:11.864
things happening within my preferred party, the very things that I had criticized as unrighteous and the other guys.

40:14.027 --> 40:19.776
A willingness to label what was clearly not aligned with the way of Jesus on the other side of the political divide as evil.

40:20.837 --> 40:26.505
And yet, when it was on my side of the aisle, I was willing to excuse it.

40:29.230 --> 40:32.274
After all, I figured God must be on my side.

40:34.402 --> 40:41.712
I've been convicted, and that conviction has led me to become an increasingly unreliable partisan.

40:43.415 --> 40:53.089
My core convictions haven't changed, but my loyalties are less and less moored to parties, politics, or personalities.

40:55.172 --> 41:02.322
The chasm between the Holy Spirit's leading and the ways the world wants to lead have become ever wider in my conscience.

41:04.290 --> 41:08.877
I don't have it on the screen, but this morning I ran across Psalm 118 verses eight and nine, it says this.

41:09.919 --> 41:14.146
It's better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in man.

41:15.448 --> 41:18.633
It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in princes.

41:20.556 --> 41:24.642
So how does our commander want us to fight in highly contentious times?

41:25.724 --> 41:31.954
Where do we position ourselves to make sure that we're on his side and not simply trying to co-opt God to our agenda?

41:33.026 --> 41:55.117
For me, it begins with a continual call to humility, a commitment to listen more and speak less, an ongoing prayer for true godly wisdom, free of prejudice, and in the places I discover pride or hypocrisy in my own heart, that there be sincere repentance.

41:56.979 --> 42:01.906
So how do we view and treat those with whom we strongly disagree?

42:02.658 --> 42:05.582
Because there are people whom I strongly disagree.

42:05.602 --> 42:07.685
I think they are wrong.

42:07.986 --> 42:09.528
Biblically, I think they are wrong.

42:10.530 --> 42:12.893
And some of those people, if we sat down and talked, they wouldn't like me.

42:13.975 --> 42:15.096
They might hate me.

42:15.216 --> 42:16.919
They might view me with contempt.

42:17.239 --> 42:18.481
So what am I supposed to do?

42:20.364 --> 42:27.555
Well, here's a direct command from our Joshua, Jesus, the command of the Lord's army.

42:27.755 --> 42:29.938
Here's what he said, Matthew, chapter five.

42:31.170 --> 42:33.814
You've heard that it was said, you shall love your neighbor and hate your enemy.

42:34.995 --> 42:37.479
But I say to you, love your enemies.

42:38.540 --> 42:52.500
Pray for those who persecute you so that you may be sons of your father who is in heaven, for he makes his son rise on the evil and on the good, the Republicans and the Democrats, and sends rain on the just and the unjust.

42:54.803 --> 42:56.305
That is what our commander calls us to do.

42:58.007 --> 43:00.050
If any earthly leader tells you otherwise,

43:01.250 --> 43:01.911
Do not follow.

43:02.752 --> 43:03.172
Let's pray.

43:10.121 --> 43:11.483
Well, I just confess for myself.

43:14.887 --> 43:21.956
I confess that sometimes in my zeal for what is right, I've gotten caught up in my own pride.

43:24.719 --> 43:30.066
Sometimes, like those Pharisees that you once talked about, I am quick to spot the specs

43:30.402 --> 43:33.525
in the eyes of others and I miss the planks in my own.

43:36.369 --> 43:47.381
Father forgive us, forgive us if we have ever made the mistake of thinking that you need to be on our side because all we need to be is on your side.

43:49.643 --> 43:51.305
Thank you that you are our deliverer.

43:52.867 --> 43:59.314
Thank you for what the cross means that you came to us in our sinfulness, in our pride,

43:59.842 --> 44:05.190
in our anger, and you did for us what we were completely unable to do for ourselves.

44:06.552 --> 44:09.957
You opened a way for us to be in your family.

44:11.740 --> 44:16.927
Thank you for that great, awesome, humbling privilege of being your children.

44:19.030 --> 44:25.139
Let me pray that you would help us to live our lives in such a way, to live our lives in such a contentious world.

44:27.403 --> 44:29.586
That the world would look at us and not just see

44:29.666 --> 44:39.458
another batch of political operatives, but they would see people, while they may not even be able to explain what's going on, they recognize that we are marching to a different drum beat.

44:41.000 --> 44:42.763
We are followers of a different commander.

44:45.146 --> 44:53.917
And Lord, may it come out in everything that we do, that we would be people who truly love, even those that we might consider enemies.

44:56.099 --> 44:57.261
I asked this in Jesus' name.

44:57.802 --> 44:58.162
Amen.

